dataDictionary.Title: PDS4 Data Dictionary
dataDictionary.Description: This document is a dump of the contents of the PDS4 Data Dictionary

class.title: Command_Execution
class.description: The Command_Execution class contains information about how the command that acquired this data was executed, such as sequence or activity.

class.title: Commanded_Parameters
class.description: The Commanded_Parameters class contains attributes used to identify or describe the commands sent to a spacecraft to perform one or more actions resulting in the acquisition of the current data product. These are distinct from similar values in the root Surface_Mission_Information class which indicate the state of the data as acquired.

class.title: Observational_Intent
class.description: Describes the intent and context of the observation.

class.title: Surface_Mission_Information
class.description: The Surface_Mission_Information class contains attributes specific to surface missions which apply across instrument types.

class.title: Telemetry
class.description: The Telemetry class contains downlink-related attributes used primarily during mission operations.

attribute.title: boot_counter
attribute.description: Counter indicating the number of times the spacecraft flight software has been booted. The intent is that this is a global counter that can uniquely identify the current FSW boot, so other counters that reset at boot time can be disambiguated.

attribute.title: command_dispatch_sclk
attribute.description: Specifies the spacecraft clock time at which the command execution was started.

attribute.title: command_sequence_number
attribute.description: The command_sequence_number attribute provides a numeric identifier for a sequence of commands sent to a spacecraft or instrument.

attribute.title: command_source_id
attribute.description: Specifies where the command that triggered acquisition of this data came from. This may be "GROUND" for ground commanding, or the name of a flight software module that initiated the request.

attribute.title: observation_id
attribute.description: The observation_id specifies a unique identifier for a scientific observation within a data set.

attribute.title: request_id
attribute.description: The request_id is used to group related datasets together by science or engineering application or theme, such as frames in a mosaic.

attribute.title: rtt_version
attribute.description: Identifies the version of the Round-Trip Tracking (RTT) system used to create metadata in this observation

attribute.title: sequence_execution_count
attribute.description: The sequence_execution_count specifies how many times this sequence has executed since the last reset of the flight computer.

attribute.title: sequence_id
attribute.description: The sequence_id identifies the command sequence used to acquire this product.

attribute.title: sequence_version_id
attribute.description: The sequence_version_id identifies which of potentially several versions of a sequence_id were used to acquire this product.

attribute.title: download_priority
attribute.description: The download_priority attribute specifies which data to downlink/transmit, based on order of importance. The ranking and meaning of specific values will vary depending on the mission, and should be defined in the mission software interface specification (SIS).

attribute.title: activity_id
attribute.description: Identifier specifying the activity this observation is a part of.

attribute.title: activity_notes
attribute.description: Provides additional notes regarding the activity.

attribute.title: campaign
attribute.description: Identifies the long-term observational campaign of which this observation is a part.

attribute.title: goal
attribute.description: Identifies the goal of this observation.

attribute.title: keyword
attribute.description: Identifies geological characteristics of a feature or target.

attribute.title: target_id
attribute.description: Identifier specifying the name or identifier of the primary target this observation is observing. This is distinct from the pds:Target class in that pds:Target typically refers to a large entity such as a planet or satellite, whereas this keyword is intended to capture much finer target information, for example a rock name or even a specific location on a rock.

attribute.title: task
attribute.description: Identifies the specific task for this observation.

attribute.title: surface_gravity
attribute.description: The surface_gravity attribute specifies the acceleration of gravity (magnitude, not direction).

attribute.title: application_id
attribute.description: The application_id (often abbreviated APID) attribute identifies the process, or source, which created the data. This can include information such as an identification of the instrument which generated the telemetry stream, its operating mode at the time of data acquisition, and any onboard compression of the data.

attribute.title: application_name
attribute.description: The application_name attribute provides the name associated with the source or process which created the data.

attribute.title: application_subtype_id
attribute.description: The application_subtype_id attribute provides further distinction (i.e., greater specificity) among application_id types.

attribute.title: auto_delete_flag
attribute.description: Indicates if the product was to be automatically deleted onboard after it is transmitted.

attribute.title: communication_session_id
attribute.description: Identifies the communication session used to acquire this data.

attribute.title: data_size
attribute.description: The data_size specifies number of bytes in the compressed data stream, not including headers.

attribute.title: download_priority
attribute.description: The download_priority attribute specifies which data to downlink/transmit, based on order of importance. The ranking and meaning of specific values will vary depending on the mission, and should be defined in the mission software interface specification (SIS).

attribute.title: earth_received_start_date_time
attribute.description: The earth_received_start_date_time attribute provides the earliest time at which any component telemetry data for a particular product was received.

attribute.title: earth_received_stop_date_time
attribute.description: The earth_received_stop_date_time attribute provides the latest time at which any component telemetry data for a particular product was received.

attribute.title: expected_packets
attribute.description: The expected_packets attribute provides the total number of telemetry packets which constitute a complete data product, i.e., a data product without missing data.

attribute.title: expected_transmission_path
attribute.description: Specifies the planned transmission path (route) for the telemetry data. See also transmission_path and communication_session_id.

attribute.title: flight_software_mode
attribute.description: Specifies the active flight software mode at the time of data product creation. Interpretation of specific modes is mission-dependent.

attribute.title: flight_software_version_id
attribute.description: The flight_software_version_id attribute identifies the version of the instrument flight software used to acquire the image.

attribute.title: product_completion_status
attribute.description: The product_completion_status attribute indicates whether or not a product is complete or is in one of a number of incomplete states. Sample values might indicate that all portions of the product have been downlinked and received correctly, that all portions have not yet been received, or that the product contains transmission errors. The specific values are mission-dependent.

attribute.title: provider_id
attribute.description: The provider_id attribute identifies the organization or subsystem that supplied the telemetry data product to the producer of the raw (EDR) PDS data product. This is typically (but not always) the organization responsible for reassembling packetized data into a single product. These may vary by mission so the permissible values should be set by the mission dictionaries.

attribute.title: received_packets
attribute.description: The received_packets attribute provides the total number of telemetry packets actually used to construct this data product. cf. expected_packets.

attribute.title: telemetry_alternate_name
attribute.description: The telemetry_alternate_name is similar to telemetry_source_name but specifies an alternate name that may be used to additionally identify the source of the telemetry data in the parent class.

attribute.title: telemetry_source_checksum
attribute.description: Specifies the checksum for the telemetry stream from which this product was derived.

attribute.title: telemetry_source_host_name
attribute.description: Specifies the name of the host venue that provided the telemetry source data used in the creation of this data set.

attribute.title: telemetry_source_name
attribute.description: The telemetry_source_name specifies the name source of the telemetry data described in the parent class.

attribute.title: telemetry_source_sclk_start
attribute.description: The telemetry_source_sclk_start attribute specifies the value of the spacecraft clock (in seconds) at the creation time of the source product from which this product was derived.

attribute.title: telemetry_source_size
attribute.description: Specifies the length in bytes of the telemetry stream from which this product was derived.

attribute.title: telemetry_source_start_time
attribute.description: The telemetry_source_start_time specifies the creation time of the source product from which this product was derived. It is the same as the telemetry_source_sclk_start converted to Spacecraft Event Time (SCET).

attribute.title: transmission_path
attribute.description: Indicates the actual transmission path (route) for the telemetry data. See also expected_transmission_path and communication_session_id.

attribute.title: transport_protocol
attribute.description: The transport_protocol attribute specifies the protocol used in the creation of the telemetry data products by the subsystem which generates the telemetry stream.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: A complete file of raw telemetry as delivered from the spacecraft to the ground.
Image delivered from instrument team with no indication of what the actual protocol was.

attribute.title: virtual_channel_id
attribute.description: Specifies the type of data flowing in the telemetry virtual channel.
